For this project, I was given the maze environment and starter code. I built the reinforcement learning part, including training the model, setting up rewards, and helping the agent 
learn how to find the treasure over time. Computer scientists build programs and systems to solve problems. This matters because technology is used everywhere and helps make things 
faster and more efficient in everyday life. When I approach problems, I break them into smaller steps, figure out what needs to be done, and test as I go. If something doesn’t work, 
I adjusted and kept improving it until it did. Ethically, making sure what I build is fair, safe, and reliable. It’s important to avoid bias and make sure users can trust the 
systems I create
